<TITLE> Govt won't let apparel sector fall sick: Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)The government will not let the readymade garment sector get sick, the finance minister said Thursday. "As much as 77 percent of our exports come from the apparel sector. We don't want it to be sick in any way. So, we are thinking about how their problems can be removed," AMA Muhith told reporters after a meeting with BGMEA and BKMEA leaders at Economic Relations Division. "The apparel industry might not be given any assistance until June in the package that has been announced. But the next budget will entail support for them." The minister said they are thinking about ways to offer a package in the new budget. "They said that the meeting they need a little help. They are facing seen shrinking orders and falling prices." Muhith said they tried to make him understand that their problems should be resolved immediately. Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association president Md. Fazlul Hoque said they hoped to get some cash aid in the next budget. Bangladesh Garment Manufacturers and Exporters Association president president Abdus Salam Murshedy was also present at the meeting. b
